Info.Name: Bileaflet House
Info.Desc: This cabin's narrowness gives people peace of mind, making it a selling point. Imagine you're a Leafe and try living in it.

Info.Name: Handmade Cottage
Info.Desc: A small cabin built using temporary materials. It has a strong DIY feel. Although small, it can be your own castle!

Info.Name: Handmade Guild Cabin
Info.Desc: An inadvertently-built guild cabin. Wind blows in through the leaky wall from time to time.

Info.Name: Guild Cabin
Info.Desc: A model guild cabin. Go weave a magnificent tale of adventure with your guildmates!

Info.Name: Master Paladin's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of successfully working hard as a Paladin and being granted the title of "Protector of Reveria." Brilliantly radiant without a single flaw!

Info.Name: Master Mercenary's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of countless achievements as a Mercenary and being granted the title of "Strongest Warrior." The scars one bears are a history of hard work.

Info.Name: Master Alchemist's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of challenging the unknown as an Alchemist and being granted the title of "Creator." No matter where one goes, stop at nothing to carry out research.

Info.Name: Master Hunter's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of defeating countless monsters as a Hunter and being granted the title of "Ultimate Hunter." Whether they're on land or in the sky, you leave prey with nowhere to run.

Info.Name: Master Tailor's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of being able to start your own brand and being granted the title of "Rising Tailoring Superstar." Starting now, a new wave is coming.

Info.Name: Master Miner's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of mining all varieties of ore as a Miner. One swing of the pickaxe breaks crystal, and two swings part the mountains.

Info.Name: Master Woodcutter's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of accomplishing much as a Woodcutter. Today, the song of the Woodcutter will echo through the depths of the forest too.

Info.Name: Master Angler's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of catching all kings of fishes in rivers, lakes, and the sea. Continue casting a line on the open sea in search of another opponent.

Info.Name: Master Blacksmith's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of becoming an expert Blacksmith known throughout Reveria. The forge's fire will never burn out.

Info.Name: Master Magician's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of receiving the spirits' blessings and learning all spells as a Magician. People will forever sing their praises.

Info.Name: Master Cook's Cottage
Info.Desc: Proof of being a Cook who consistently makes five-star dishes that bring tasters to tears. Their ability is recognized by all of Reveria.

Info.Name: Master Carpenter's Cottage
Info.Desc: A house that only Carpenters who have been awarded the title of "Ultra-Carpenter of Godlike Skill" can live in. It can withstand any shaking.

Info.Name: Log Cabin
Info.Desc: A My Cabin built for those who pursue nature. It lets you feel the warmth of the wood. It's quite roomy inside.

Info.Name: Simple Hut
Info.Desc: A small, sophisticated, basically functional cottage. It's perfect for one person to live in.

Info.Name: Dosh Hut
Info.Desc: An advanced two-story cottage with its own garden. Feel what it's like to be a grown-up!

Info.Name: Large Log Cabin
Info.Desc: A spacious cabin with two floors. The smell of wood can help you sleep better.

Info.Name: Large Simple Hut
Info.Desc: A spacious house that can hold a lot of furniture. It's suitable for a family to live in. Maybe it's a bit luxurious for a single person?

Info.Name: Royal Cabin
Info.Desc: The largest My Cabin. Both floors are very spacious! Suitable for those who seek the ultimate sense of residence.

Info.Name: Yo-kai Hut
Info.Desc: A mansion that's been uninhabited for decades. Rumor has it that it's haunted.

Info.Name: Pumpkin Hut
Info.Desc: A cottage made from a huge, hollowed-out pumpkin. There's a clear scent of pumpkin in the room.

Info.Name: Spook Bench
Info.Desc: A chair famous for (allegedly) letting the user take pictures with spooks. It seems that the spooks are even willing to listen to your troubles.

Info.Name: Red Deity's Statue
Info.Desc: A statue of the red God made of gold. A gift to someone who turns their Life into strength. You may get a reward if you pray to it.

Info.Name: Blue Deity's Statue
Info.Desc: A statue of the blue God made of gold. A gift to someone who turns their Life into wisdom. You may get a reward if you pray to it.

Info.Name: Refreshing Tree
Info.Desc: A small tree that you can lean on and relax under. You can have a good picnic beside it! Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Reunion Tree
Info.Desc: A relaxing tree for a 3-person picnic. Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Chocolate & Refreshing Tree
Info.Desc: A chocolate-coated tree very popular with deserts parties. Leaning on the tree, you can smell a faint, sweet fragrance. Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Tree Shade
Info.Desc: Sit on a stump and spend time relaxing with your friends!

Info.Name: Double Bench
Info.Desc: For you, who wants to spend your leisure time with a certain someone. Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Simple Bench
Info.Desc: For you, who wants to enjoy a nice lunch break. Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Relaxing Swing
Info.Desc: Relive your childhood and enjoy life! A swing for one. Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Swing for Two
Info.Desc: Relax and be happy! A swing for two. Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Yellow Flowerbed
Info.Desc: So long as you water this flowerbed, wonderful "Yellowbells" will bloom. It's indispensable to Tailors.

Info.Name: Green Flowerbed
Info.Desc: So long as you water this flowerbed, wonderful "Greenbells" will bloom. It's indispensable to Tailors.

Info.Name: Blue Flowerbed
Info.Desc: So long as you water this flowerbed, wonderful "Bluebells" will bloom. It's indispensable to Tailors.

Info.Name: Black Flowerbed
Info.Desc: So long as you water this flowerbed, wonderful "Blackbells" will bloom. It's indispensable to Tailors.

Info.Name: Red Flowerbed
Info.Desc: So long as you water this flowerbed, wonderful "Redbells" will bloom. It's indispensable to Tailors.

Info.Name: White Flowerbed
Info.Desc: So long as you water this flowerbed, wonderful "Whitebells" will bloom. It's indispensable to Tailors.

Info.Name: Purple Flowerbed
Info.Desc: So long as you water this flowerbed, wonderful "Purplebells" will bloom. It's indispensable to Tailors.

Info.Name: Flower Garden
Info.Desc: A huge flowerbed with colorful flowers. With it, you can become a master of gardening.

Info.Name: Festive Tree
Info.Desc: A Festive Tree that is smartly made out of a giant tree.

Info.Name: Giant Festive Tree
Info.Desc: A Giant Festive Tree perfect for celebrating Xmas with everyone.

Info.Name: Pumpkin Field
Info.Desc: A small vegetable garden for households to grow sweet pumpkins. Namona's water is the secret to their sweetness!

Info.Name: Sleeping Dragon
Info.Desc: A large dragon that sleeps soundly in Namona. Please don't wake it up. Gently sit down.

Info.Name: Weird Cabin
Info.Desc: A small tree that's not quite like a common plant. There seems to be a situation where the fruit unknowingly disappears. Maybe a Joy Event will happen?

Info.Name: Plushling Cafe
Info.Desc: A place where friends in the village can relax while chatting. You can also smell the aroma of beans.

Info.Name: Plushling Bar
Info.Desc: Drink a cup today and be full of energy tomorrow! A social place for adults that only opens at night. The Plushling bartender who's good at listening is the secret to its popularity.

Info.Name: Stardust Observatory
Info.Desc: A beautiful observatory with a huge telescope. Every night, the stars shine bright. A recreation facility where residents can come and stargaze.

Info.Name: Strange Monument
Info.Desc: A strange monument as brilliant as gold. Looking at its complicated, strange shape gives you a burst of creativity.

Info.Name: Ancient Great Tree
Info.Desc: A huge tree said to have lived for thousands of years. Chatting under this tree makes one feel they can gain a lot of experience.

Info.Name: Festival Stage
Info.Desc: A festival stage favored by the Plushlings. Enjoy a festive atmosphere alongside village friends!

Info.Name: Inn
Info.Desc: Sweet dreams relieve fatigue! A resting place for the residents of the village. After being built, it can be used by allies.

Info.Name: Dining Table
Info.Desc: A restaurant that provides take-out services. It can provide many delicacies. Also purchases homemade dishes at high prices.

Info.Name: Arms Shop
Info.Desc: A shop where weapons and armor are traded. Purchases equipment at a high price. Very useful for Blacksmiths and Carpenters!

Info.Name: General Store
Info.Desc: A shop that trades healing items and tools. After leveling it up, the shop will provide a richer product lineup.

Info.Name: Furniture Shop
Info.Desc: A shop selling all kinds of furniture to decorate rooms. Also purchases furniture at high prices. There will be more furniture available once it's leveled up!

Info.Name: Meat/Egg Shop
Info.Desc: A shop that sells juicy meat for cooking. Purchases all kinds of meat at high prices. A must-have for Cooks!

Info.Name: Fish Store
Info.Desc: A shop selling all kinds of fresh, live fish. Purchases all kinds of fish at high prices. An indispensable Life facility for Anglers!

Info.Name: Veggie/Fruit Store
Info.Desc: A shop selling all kinds of fresh vegetables for cooking. Purchases all kinds of vegetables at high prices. A must-have for Cooks!

Info.Name: Ore Store
Info.Desc: A shop that sells all kinds of ores needed for forging. An indispensable Life facility for Miners! It's also very convenient for enhancing weapons and armor.

Info.Name: Leather/Timber Store
Info.Desc: A shop selling all kinds of wood and sturdy beast hides. An indispensable Life facility for Carpenters! It's also very convenient for enhancing staffs and bows.

Info.Name: Suspicious Store
Info.Desc: A shop that trades all kinds of exotic materials needed for alchemy. Purchase all kinds of gemstones at high prices. Build one without hesitation.

Info.Name: Fashion Boutique
Info.Desc: A shop that trades all kinds of beautiful clothes. Purchases outfits at a high price. The clothing here can be worn by people of almost all Lives!

Info.Name: Drapery Shop
Info.Desc: A shop selling silk and fabrics needed by Tailors. Purchases fabrics at high prices. There will be more items available once it's leveled up!

Info.Desc: An advanced facility that allows 3 Anglers to "work" at the same time. As long as you have this, wait for a good harvest.

Info.Desc: An advanced facility that allows 3 Blacksmiths to work on requests at the same time. Forge a lot of equipment and make a lot of money!

Info.Name: Carpenter Atelier
Info.Desc: An advanced facility that allows 3 Carpenters to work on requests at the same time. Make all kinds of furniture and equipment!

Info.Name: Tailor Atelier
Info.Desc: An advanced facility that allows 3 Tailors to work on requests at the same time. With lots of clothes, you can dress more colorfully!

Info.Name: Alchemy Lab
Info.Desc: An advanced facility that allows 3 Alchemists to work on requests at the same time. As long as you have it, you'll always have enough healing items!

Info.Name: Large Dining Table
Info.Desc: An advanced Dining Table that allows 3 Cooks to work on requests at the same time. No matter how many dishes you order, you'll get all of them!

Info.Name: Kingdom Training Ground
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Paladins to "work" at the same time. The XP gains and items obtained are also of the highest level.

Info.Name: Berserk Arena
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Mercenaries to "work" at the same time. The XP gains and items obtained are also of the highest level.

Info.Name: Pro Range
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Hunters to "work" at the same time. The XP gains and items obtained are also of the highest level.

Info.Name: Philosopher's College
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Magicians to "work" at the same time. The XP gains and items obtained are also of the highest level.

Info.Name: Treasure's Digsite
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Miners to work at the same time. Even very rare ore can be obtained in large quantities!

Info.Name: Great Spirit's Lumbermill
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Woodcutters to work at the same time. The most advanced wood is all yours!

Info.Name: Fishing Site
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Anglers to work at the same time. It's said that you can catch the big fish of your dreams here!

Info.Name: Famous Artisan's Smithy
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Blacksmiths to work at the same time. Use the skills of artisans to make more excellent equipment!

Info.Name: Carpenter Atelier
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Carpenters to work at the same time. Make the most upscale furniture and equipment!

Info.Name: Charismatic Tailor Atelier
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Tailors to work at the same time. Make lots of glamorous outfits!

Info.Name: Forbidden Alchemy Lab
Info.Desc: A top-tier facility that allows 3 Alchemists to work at the same time. Super-practical recovery items and bombs are born here!

Info.Name: Deluxe Dining Table
Info.Desc: A Deluxe dining table that allows 3 Cooks to work at the same time. Hurry up and make the highest quality dishes that will tickle your tastebuds!

Info.Name: Scarecrow Training Ground
Info.Desc: A "work" facility for Paladins. Grants XP through training and various items through exploration of different places.

Info.Name: Claymore Training Ground
Info.Desc: A "work" facility for Mercenaries. Grants XP through training and various items through exploration of different places.

Info.Name: Apple Range
Info.Desc: A "work" facility for Hunters. Grants XP through training and various items through exploration of different places.

Info.Name: Magic Training Ground
Info.Desc: A "work" facility for Magicians. Grants XP through training and various items through exploration of different places.

Info.Name: Mine
Info.Desc: A "work" facility for Miners. You can obtain ores such as copper and iron required for crafting equipment.

Info.Name: Lumbermill
Info.Desc: A "work" facility for Carpenters. Grants tons of wood, making it great for Carpenters!

Info.Name: Fishing Pool
Info.Desc: A "work" facility for Anglers. You can catch all kinds of fish. Maybe you'll catch something other than fish from time to time?

Info.Desc: A facility for "Forging" that lets you craft/enhance equipment. If there's a Blacksmith there, you can also request work.

Info.Desc: A facility for "Carpentry" that lets you craft/enhance equipment. If there's a Carpenter there, you can also request work.

Info.Name: Tailor Shop
Info.Desc: A facility for Tailoring that lets you craft/enhance clothing. If there's a Tailor there, you can also request work.

Info.Name: Medical Lab
Info.Desc: A facility for Alchemy lets you craft healing items and bombs. If there's an Alchemist there, you can also request work.

Info.Name: Sky Kitchen
Info.Desc: A facility for Cooking lets you cook various dishes. If there's a Cook there, you can also request work.

Info.Name: Castele Waterway
Info.Desc: A small channel with babbling water. Just listening to the sound of water makes people feel healed.

Info.Name: Castele Waterway with Bridges
Info.Desc: A waterway with a strong bridge. Of course you can cross it by walking on the bridge. Enjoy your stroll!

Info.Desc: Flowerbeds that adorn the streets of Castele. The size is small, making it easy to install. It looks gorgeous no matter where you place it.
